result.name: Hong Kong Jockey Club Happy Valley Racecourse

reviews.text: Wonderful jogging track and free spacious showers/changing room available. When there's no horse racing, people can run on the concrete road right next to the racecourse. Very popular with runners.
Very cool place, happy they have the Wednesday night races and super happy that I caught the last one of the season. Lots of promotional people, but they were all super friendly

Really good experience when going to Hong Kong. Beware of the smokers outside if you’re not into that kind of thing. There is an entrance fee of 100. Otherwise, it’s really fun putting down a bet on horses and playing on the possibly of winning some money!

Came here to visit, as I have never been even though I visit Hong Kong every year. I enjoyed my visit at the Hong Kong Jockey Club at Happy Valley. The museum was free to enter, but it was small. Still enjoyed the museum. The view of the racecourse is breathtaking. The restaurant there looks very posh, but didn't eat there. You can go inside, entrance fee is only $5

Wednesday night race meetings are always fun. Impressive surroundings, good atmosphere, reasonable beer selection and prices. Placing bets is straightforward and staff will assist you. Highly recommended.
